title: [CRA-RxJS-SC] Refractor Repo sub-header & tab navigation
body:
Resolves: #337 

1. I refactored the routing in `index.tsx` for the individual repo page. Allowing for routing for PRs, issues and code, under one AuthGuard.
2. I refactored the sub-header to correctly get the right number of issues using `https://api.github.com/search` instead of `/issues` as used before. This also allows for future  pagination and filtering for PRs and issues.
3. I added functionality for active tabs based on routes in the subheader
4. Fix: Changed all fill-rule to fillRule for SVGs


https://www.loom.com/share/7390f113d8e6431b8ad307b45878d31c

title: [Angular-NgRx-SCSS] Amplify deployed site fixes
body:
**UPDATE: Removed small fixes, to be adjusted at a later date. This PR now only makes a small adjustment for the Amplify deployed site.**

Trying to fix the deployed version of the site! Plus small fixes to the styles / data that already exist.

- The main fix is to adjust the production "apiUrl" to match what it should be. It's hard to test this with the preview deploy since it doesn't redirect to the main site - I think we'll want a new ticket / issue for changing how the redirect works, because I don't know that the preview deploys will work without it. But I think that should be a separate issue.
- Small style fix so the main login page fills the whole screen
- Small data fix so the user's list of repos is sorted by created date, which matches the other showcases
